<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Covetous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Covetous,</orth> 1) desirous; followed by <emph>of</emph> or <emph>for</emph>: <cit><quote>c. of wisdom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of praise,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.248" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 248</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>for gold,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 24</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) absol. greedy of gain, avaricious: <bibl n="shak. son 134.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 134, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.515" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 515</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 79</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>